column23: Manoa Honey Company has avaiable limited quanties of both single nectar source honeys and blended honeys gathered by our bee in apiaries located at 7 sites on the island of O'ahu.  Our bees collect nectar from wild flowers in the pristine Ko'olau Mountains, the lush valleys of the Windward Side and the coastal plains of 'Ewa and Wai'anae.  Our honeys are not processed, heated, or filtered and contain all of the enzymes, minerals, vitamins, antibiotics and antioxidants put there by the bees.  We also make prize winning meads, honey-based beers and honey tropical fruit based wines (melomels, pyments, and cysers) and wonderful, aromatic, hand-dipped pure beeswax candles.

column23: Lehualani (lay-hoo-uh-la-nee) Farm's 100% pure Kona Coffee.  All the coffee we offer is grown, hand-picked, processed and sun-dried on our 3.8 acre farm at the 1700' elevation on the leeward slopes of Mauna Loa.  The name Lehualani comes from the red lehua flower of the ohia trees that grow on our farm, and "lani" means heaven in Hawaiian.  Visitors to our farm are always welcome.  Kona Coffee is prized all over the world as a gourmet coffee--rich, smooth, and delicious.  We believe our coffee is the best Kona coffee you can buy, and we guarantee it.  If you aren't totally satisfied, please return it for a full refund.  We ship 1 pound bags, whole bean, medium or dark roast anywhere in the world.  We offer coffee in 1 lb bags, 1/2 lb bags, and 5 lb bags.  TOLL FREE 1-888-917-9577

As a traditional, culturally-significant food, Pele leaves are also highly nutritious, containing significant amounts of iron, magnesium, calcium, vitamin A, vitamin C, and protein (5%).  A great alternative to Lu'au (taro) leaves.  The scientific name is "hibiscus manihot".
